{"key":"post-8522838","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8522838</id>\n<content>Agreed.&amp;nbsp; Stack the lids and drill all twelve at once.&amp;nbsp; Another tip is to drill the opposite direction they'll sit on the jars so the burrs don't puncture your filter.&amp;nbsp; Since I use the lids rubber side up to make removal easier, I drill down from the rubber side, not the way they come shipped.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you use 1/4&quot; holes, don't drill more than one.&amp;nbsp; Too much air will cause early pinning and drying of the grains.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8523317</next>\n<prev>8522807</prev>\n<first>8521948</first>\n<last>8526090</last>\n<when>1213455020</when>\n<utime>06/14/08 05:50 PM</utime>\n</post>"}